snippet: The approval of nearly 900 units in a disputed area of Jerusalem was officially published, and the Israeli military said it had intercepted a rocket fired from Egypt.
abstract: Israeli Interior Ministry publishes final approval of nearly 900 new apartments in contested part of Jerusalem, new affront to Palestinians on eve of resumed peace talks; separately, Israeli military says it has intercepted rocket fired from Egypt.

byline.original: By ISABEL KERSHNER and RICK GLADSTONE
byline.contributor: Isabel Kershner reported from Jerusalem, and Rick Gladstone from New York. Michael R. Gordon contributed reporting from Washington.

lead_paragraph: The approval of nearly 900 units in a disputed area of Jerusalem was officially published, and the Israeli military said it had intercepted a rocket fired from Egypt.

headline.main: On Eve of Talks, Israel Approves More Housing and Stops a Rocket
headline.print_headline: On Eve of Talks, Israel Approves More Housing and Stops a Rocket
